#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""
Bush Glue STT bench harness.

Drives each STT engine adapter against a labelled audio corpus and emits a CSV
with WER + latency + CPU + RAM per (utterance, engine, run). This is the
single-most-important week-1 artifact: it's how we pick the recognizer per
eng review §6.

Usage:
    bush-stt-bench --corpus <dir> --engine <name>[,<name>...] --output <csv> \\
        [--model <path>] [--repeat N] [--warmup N] [--language en]

The corpus dir must contain per-utterance WAV files plus a transcripts.tsv
ground-truth file:
    <wav_filename>\\t<ground_truth_text>\\t<condition_label>

Engines are loaded lazily; an engine that cannot be imported (module missing)
is skipped with a warning so the bench remains robust as new engines arrive.

Required Python deps (NOT in pyproject — bench is a dev tool):
    pip install jiwer>=3.0    # WER / CER metrics
    pip install psutil>=5.9   # CPU + RAM monitoring
    pip install soxr>=0.5     # resampling for non-16 kHz inputs (already in services/audio)

If jiwer or psutil are missing the bench keeps running with sentinel -1 values
in the affected columns and prints a one-line install hint.
"""
import os
import sys

